title: Tennessee RB Kelly expected back at practice Thursday
text:
Tennessee RB John Kelly expected back at practice Thursday after getting taken to hospital THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   1:14 pmLast   1:14 pm   
People: 
Tennessee (480) 

KNOXVILLE, Tennessee — Tennessee running back John Kelly is expected to return to practice this week after getting taken to the hospital during Tuesday's workout. 
Volunteers coach Butch Jones said Wednesday during the Southeastern Conference coaches teleconference that Kelly "had some tingling going down his body" during Tennessee's Tuesday afternoon practice. Jones said Kelly was transported to the hospital for precautionary reasons. 
Jones said Kelly underwent an MRI and CT scan and that "everything has passed, everything has been good." Jones said "I can assure everyone that John is doing well" and added that he anticipates Kelly participating in Thursday's practice. 
Kelly, a freshman from Detroit, has 21 carries for 88 yards this season. 
Tennessee (3-3, 1-2 SEC) has this week off before visiting No. 10 Alabama (5-1, 2-1) on Oct. 24.
